Key Match Events: Austria beats Netherlands 3-2 in a thrilling match.
Donyell Malen scored an own goal in the 6th minute.
Cody Gakpo equalized for Netherlands in the 47th minute.
Romano Schmid scored Austria's second goal in the 59th minute, deflected in by Stefan De Vrij.
Memphis Depay scored for Netherlands in the 75th minute.
Marcel Sabitzer scored the winning goal for Austria in the 80th minute.
Post-Match Reflections: Austria now faces the second-placed team from Group F.
The Netherlands have qualified for the knockout stages as a best third-placed side and will face England if the Three Lions top Group C.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria's counter-pressing strategy was highly effective.
Netherlands manager Ronald Koeman made a substitution after just 35 minutes to change the dynamics of the game.
Austria's victory marks their first win against Netherlands since May 1990.
